# Nginx — Angular SPA routing

When adding or editing Nginx config for this app:

## Build

- Project: **Masajid-Work** → output **`dist/Masajid-Work`** (browser builder; **not** `…/browser`).
- Domain root deploy: `npm run build` or `ng build --configuration production` (`baseHref: /` is set in `angular.json` build options).
- GitHub Pages uses **`github-pages`** config (`baseHref: /Masajid-Work/`) — run `npm run build:gh-pages`.

## Site config (required)

```nginx
root /var/www/masajid/dist/Masajid-Work;
index index.html;

location / {
    try_files $uri $uri/ /index.html;
}
```

## API routes

Define **`location`** blocks for backend paths **before** the `/` fallback (e.g. `/SystemAPIs/`, `/api/`). Do not let `try_files` swallow API requests.

## After editing

```bash
sudo nginx -t
sudo systemctl reload nginx
```

Reference: **`deploy/nginx/masajid-work.conf`**, **`deploy.md`** (Nginx section).
